1. e4 { [%clk 1:30:42] } 1... c5 { [%clk 1:30:39] } 2. Nf3 { [%clk 1:30:56] } 2... Nc6 { [%clk 1:30:56] } 3. Bb5 { [%clk 1:30:57] } (3. d4 { I was more expecting this }) 3... d6 { I've never played 3...d6 before, but I wanted to surprise my opponent since he only recently started playing the Rossolimo. } { [%clk 1:30:52] } 4. O-O { [%clk 1:30:53] } 4... Bd7 { [%clk 1:31:12] } 5. Re1 { [%clk 1:29:52] } 5... a6 { [%clk 1:31:04] } 6. Bxc6 { [%clk 1:29:59] } 6... Bxc6 { [%clk 1:31:12] } 7. d4 { [%clk 1:30:15] } 7... cxd4 { [%clk 1:30:59] } 8. Nxd4 { [%clk 1:29:51] } 8... Rc8 { [%clk 1:30:53] } 9. c4 { [%clk 1:27:52] } 9... Nf6 { [%clk 1:28:32] } 10. Nc3 { [%clk 1:26:17] } 10... e6 { [%clk 1:26:52] } 11. b3 { [%clk 1:21:03] } 11... Be7 { [%clk 1:25:47] } 12. Bb2 { [%clk 1:17:25] } 12... O-O { Even though white should be slightly better, I was content with how the opening went. My opponent usually likes to go for sharp/concrete lines in the open Sicilian, and this is wayyyy more positional and strategic. Note the time usage on the next several moves. } { [%clk 1:25:14] } 13. Qd2 { [%clk 1:13:23] } 13... Re8 { [%clk 1:17:35] } 14. Rad1 { [%clk 1:10:33] } 14... Qc7 { [%clk 1:14:41] } 15. h3 { [%clk 0:52:01] } 15... b6 { [%clk 1:07:50] } 16. Nxc6 { [%clk 0:42:43] } 16... Qxc6 { [%clk 1:08:06] } 17. a4 { [%clk 0:41:26] } 17... Nd7 { [%clk 1:01:21] } 18. Qd4 { [%clk 0:29:39] } 18... Qc5 { [%clk 0:56:21] } 19. Nd5 { [%clk 0:20:56] } 19... Bf8 { [%clk 0:54:20] } 20. Ne3 { [%clk 0:21:17] } 20... Qxd4 { [%clk 0:49:52] } 21. Bxd4 { [%clk 0:21:41] } 21... Nc5 { [%clk 0:50:05] } 22. Rb1 { [%clk 0:21:48] } 22... b5 { A safer option } { [%clk 0:39:10] } (22... Nxe4!? { leads to lots more complications } 23. Bxb6 d5!? { crazy engine idea } 24. cxd5 Bb4 25. Rf1 Nd2 26. d6 Bxd6 27. Nc4 { somehow this is still equal }) 23. Bxc5 { [%clk 0:17:54] } 23... Rxc5 { [%clk 0:39:24] } 24. b4 { [%clk 0:16:48] } 24... Rc6 { [%clk 0:39:03] } 25. cxb5 { [%clk 0:16:32] } 25... axb5 { [%clk 0:39:27] } 26. a5 { Even though white achieves a defended outside passed pawn, black is able to dominate the only open file. The resulting endgame is quite drawish... } { [%clk 0:14:00] } 26... Rec8 { [%clk 0:38:30] } 27. Red1 { [%clk 0:11:54] } 27... Be7 { [%clk 0:37:08] } 28. Kf1 { [%clk 0:11:21] } 28... Kf8 { [%clk 0:35:03] } 29. Ke2 { [%clk 0:10:25] } 29... Bg5 { [%clk 0:34:05] } 30. Rd3 { [%clk 0:09:01] } 30... Ke7 { [%clk 0:33:23] } 31. Rbd1 { [%clk 0:08:38] } 31... R8c7 { [%clk 0:31:29] } 32. g3 { [%clk 0:08:36] } 32... Bxe3 { [%clk 0:29:16] } 33. Kxe3 { [%clk 0:09:02] } 33... Ra6 { I think I offered a draw around here, but my opponent tried to "torture" me for many moves. There wasn't much either side could do... } { [%clk 0:29:07] } 34. R1d2 { [%clk 0:07:08] } 34... Rc4 { [%clk 0:27:37] } 35. Rb2 { [%clk 0:07:31] } 35... Kd7 { [%clk 0:23:30] } 36. f3 { [%clk 0:07:31] } 36... Kc7 { [%clk 0:23:09] } 37. h4 { [%clk 0:05:57] } 37... Rac6 { [%clk 0:21:08] } 38. h5 { [%clk 0:04:20] } 38... Rc1 { [%clk 0:20:26] } 39. g4 { [%clk 0:04:10] } 39... h6 { [%clk 0:19:41] } 40. Kf4 { [%clk 0:03:36] } 40... f6 { [%clk 0:17:18] } 41. Rbb3 { [%clk 0:01:44] } 41... Kb7 { [%clk 0:15:08] } 42. Rb2 { [%clk 0:28:55] } 42... Kc7 { [%clk 0:44:47] } 43. Ke3 { [%clk 0:26:07] } 43... Re1+ { [%clk 0:44:17] } 44. Kd2 { [%clk 0:25:55] } 44... Rf1 { [%clk 0:43:14] } 45. Rbb3 { [%clk 0:25:51] } 45... Rf2+ { [%clk 0:42:54] } 46. Ke3 { [%clk 0:26:18] } 46... Rfc2 { [%clk 0:42:48] } 47. Rd2 { [%clk 0:24:39] } 47... Rc1 { [%clk 0:42:29] } 48. Rbb2 { [%clk 0:18:12] } 48... R1c3+ { [%clk 0:41:43] } 49. Rd3 { [%clk 0:16:40] } 49... Rc1 { [%clk 0:41:28] } 50. Kd2 { [%clk 0:15:35] } 50... Rf1 { [%clk 0:41:12] } 51. Rdb3 { [%clk 0:14:47] } 51... Kb7 { [%clk 0:39:16] } 52. Ke3 { [%clk 0:14:40] } 52... Re1+ { [%clk 0:38:57] } 53. Re2 { [%clk 0:14:38] } 53... Rec1 { [%clk 0:38:25] } 54. Rd2 { [%clk 0:14:27] } 54... Kc7 { [%clk 0:37:34] } 55. Kf4 { [%clk 0:14:29] } 55... Kb7 { [%clk 0:32:58] } 56. Rbd3 { [%clk 0:11:58] } 56... Kc7 { [%clk 0:36:11] } 57. Rb2 { [%clk 0:12:22] } 57... Kb7 { [%clk 0:35:41] } 58. Kg3 { [%clk 0:12:14] } 58... Rg1+ { [%clk 0:35:07] } 59. Kf4 { [%clk 0:10:47] } 59... Rgc1 { [%clk 0:35:22] } 60. Rbd2 { [%clk 0:10:36] } 60... Kc7 { [%clk 0:35:31] } 61. Ra2 { [%clk 0:09:40] } 61... Kb8 { [%clk 0:31:14] } 62. Rb2 { At this point I claimed a draw with my next move being Kb7, and my opponent accepted without asking to verify the 3-fold. Overall, a solid game from both sides and pretty mistake-free. } { [%clk 0:07:28] } *


