uld be preferred with black's pieces lacking harmony. }) 31. Bxg7 Kxg7 32. Qg5+ Kf8 33. Qh6+ Ke7 34. e5! $18 { One of the pretty lines I calculated }) 30. f5 { [%clk 0:23:27] } 30... f6 { [%clk 0:08:44] } 31. Qg6+ { [%clk 0:21:40] } 31... Bg7 { [%clk 0:08:58] } 32. Bxb3 { [%clk 0:17:07] } 32... cxb3 { [%clk 0:09:08] } 33. Ra6 { [%clk 0:15:27] } 33... Na4 { [%clk 0:06:23] } 34. Rxd6 { when I played this, I thought I'm on the verge of winning, but it's really not so simple. } { [%clk 0:14:18] } 34... Rf8 { [%clk 0:06:00] } 35. h5 { [%clk 0:11:49] } (35. Nxb3 Qc4 36. Nd2 Qd3 37. Qg3 { one of the engine's lines, but this is difficult to assess. }) 35... Be8 { [%clk 0:06:12] } 36. Qg4? { After this, the momentum swings in black's favor } { [%clk 0:12:18] } (36. Qg3 { The only move to not be worse. It's more important to keep e3 defended rather than h5. } 36... Nxb2 (36... Bxh5 37. Nxb3) 37. Nxb3 Nc4 38. Rda6) 36... Nxb2 { [%clk 0:05:03] } 37. Rc1 { [%clk 0:02:18] } (37. Nxb3 Qxc3 { If the white queen was on g3, there would be Nc5. However, this is just losing for white }) 37... Qc7 { There are lots of eval swings with the next several moves. 'Tis the nature of time pressure in a crazy position! } { [%clk 0:03:55] } 38. Ra6 { [%clk 0:02:16] } 38... Kh7 { [%clk 0:03:15] } 39. Nxb3 { [%clk 0:01:31] } 39... Nc4 { [%clk 0:03:16] } 40. Bf2 { [%clk 0:00:52] } 40... Bh6 { [%clk 0:02:27] } 41. Rca1 { [%clk 0:27:52] } (41. Re1 { preventing Ne3 would have been better. White is still clearly worse though } 41... Rg8) 41... Ne3 { [%clk 0:25:41] } 42. Qe2 { [%clk 0:19:49] } 42... Qxc3 { [%clk 0:24:52] } 43. R6a3 { holding on for dear life } { [%clk 0:16:28] } 43... Qc4 { [%clk 0:18:08] } (43... b4 44. Rc1 { my idea. This still wins for black in multiple ways though }) 44. Qf3 { [%clk 0:11:28] } 44... b4 { [%clk 0:09:23] } 45. Na5 { [%clk 0:11:07] } 45... bxa3 { black's position is so good, he can afford to sac the queen! } { [%clk 0:08:24] } 46. Nxc4 { [%clk 0:10:16] } 46... Nxc4 { [%clk 0:08:25] } 47. Qc3 { [%clk 0:08:59] } 47... Bb5 { [%clk 0:07:57] } 48. Kh2 { [%clk 0:07:08] } 48... Ra8 { [%clk 0:06:17] } 49. Ra2 { [%clk 0:05:37] } 49... Bf4+ { [%clk 0:04:37] } 50. g3 { [%clk 0:04:52] } 50... Bd2 { [%clk 0:04:57] } 51. Qb3 { [%clk 0:04:54] } 51... Bc1 { [%clk 0:05:05] } 52. Bc5 { [%clk 0:03:56] } 52... Rc8 { [%clk 0:04:00] } 53. Be7 { [%clk 0:03:05] } 53... Ba6 { [%clk 0:02:00] } 54. Qa4 { [%clk 0:03:20] } 54... Bb5 { [%clk 0:01:59] } 55. Qb3 { [%clk 0:02:30] } 55... Kg7? { [%clk 0:01:13] } (55... Rxe7 56. Qxb5 Ra7 { should be winning for black }) 56. d6! { white is back in the game! } { [%clk 0:02:04] } 56... Kf7 { [%clk 0:01:20] } 57. d7! { [%clk 0:01:13] } 57... Rxd7 { [%clk 0:01:13] } 58. Bxa3 { [%clk 0:01:23] } 58... Bxa3 { [%clk 0:01:04] } 59. Qxb5 { [%clk 0:01:29] } 59... Rdc7 { [%clk 0:01:10] } 60. Qa6 { [%clk 0:00:45] } (60. h6 { Apparently this is nearly winning for white. }) 60... Bd6 { [%clk 0:01:18] } 61. g4 { [%clk 0:00:43] } (61. Rc2! { Another missed win }) 61... Kg7 { [%clk 0:01:15] } 62. Rc2 { [%clk 0:00:51] } 62... Rc6 { [%clk 0:01:03] } 63. Qa4 { [%clk 0:01:15] } 63... Bf8 { [%clk 0:01:11] } 64. Qb5 { [%clk 0:00:51] } 64... Kh6 { [%clk 0:01:20] } 65. Kh3 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 65... Bg7 { [%clk 0:00:47] } 66. Qd5 { [%clk 0:00:56] } 66... R8c7 { [%clk 0:00:50] } 67. g5+ { [%clk 0:00:43] } (67. Qg8! { another missed win! } 67... Kg5 68. h6 Kxh6 69. Rh2 Kg5 70. Kg3) 67... fxg5 { [%clk 0:00:36] } 68. Rxc4 { [%clk 0:00:50] } 68... Rxc4 { [%clk 0:00:57] } 69. Qe6+ { [%clk 0:01:07] } 69... Kh7 { [%clk 0:01:25] } 70. Qg6+ { [%clk 0:01:08] } 70... Kg8 { [%clk 0:01:44] } 71. Qe8+ { [%clk 0:00:50] } 71... Bf8 { [%clk 0:01:21] } 72. Qe6+ { [%clk 0:00:50] } 72... Kh7 { [%clk 0:01:35] } 73. Qg6+ { [%clk 0:00:44] } 73... Kh8 { [%clk 0:02:03] } 74. Qe8 { [%clk 0:00:57] } 74... Kg8 { [%clk 0:01:10] } 75. Qe6+ { [%clk 0:01:00] } 75... Kh7 { [%clk 0:01:30] } 76. Qg6+ { [%clk 0:01:24] } 76... Kh8 { [%clk 0:01:56] } 77. Qe8 { [%clk 0:01:51] } 77..